## 2026-04-03 - Core validateColorModifiers silently drops valid mix operations
- Removed the spurious `typeof obj.amount === 'number' && isFinite(obj.amount)` precondition from the `mix` branch in `validateColorModifiers`. The `mix` type in `ColorModifierOp` only requires `color` (string) and `ratio` (number) — `amount` is not part of its schema and is not read by `applyColorModifiers`. A valid `{type:'mix', color:'#fff', ratio:0.5}` was being silently dropped.
- Updated tests: removed `amount: 0` from the mix entry in "returns valid ops unchanged"; updated "drops mix entries missing color or ratio" to not pass spurious `amount`; added explicit regression test "accepts mix without amount field".
- Files changed: `packages/core/src/color-modifier.ts` ~L32-39, `packages/core/src/__tests__/color-modifier.test.ts` ~L114, ~L136-145

