## 2026-04-03 - Generator service does not clear generatorErrors on delete
- Fixed two bugs in `packages/server/src/services/generator-service.ts`:
  1. `delete()` now calls `this.generatorErrors.delete(id)` so stale error state doesn't leak if a new generator is created with the same ID later.
  2. `runForSourceToken()` now tracks `failedIds` (a Set) and skips any downstream generator whose `sourceToken` starts with a failed upstream generator's `targetGroup + '.'`. Skipped generators get their own error entry ("Skipped: upstream generator failed") and a `generator-error` event so the UI reflects the skip. Previously, downstream generators executed against stale/unchanged output.

